      "rendered": "25 Online Gift Stores That Benefit Nonprofits"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Updated: <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2019/10/20/xx-online-stores-that-benefit-nonprofits-and-the-greater-good/\">View 2019 Holiday Shopping Guide</a></h2>\n<p>According to Shop.org&#8217;s annual <strong><a style=\"color: #0062a0;\" href=\"https://nrf.com/resources/retail-library/eholiday-2014-pre-holiday-retailer-and-consumer-survey-results\">Holiday 2014 Pre-Holiday Retailer and Consumer Study</a></strong>,<span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\">\u00a0two out of five U.S. consumers started their holiday shopping in October. </span><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\">The study also found that o</span>nline shoppers plan to spend 16 percent more than brick-and-mortar shoppers this holiday season on\u00a0gifts, decorations, greeting cards, and food. All told, online shoppers expect to spend an average of $931.75.\u00a0Conscious consumers can channel some of their spending power into creating good in the world by shopping at any of the 25 online stores listed below.\u00a0<span style=\"color: #383838;\">Please give back this holiday season by shopping ethically.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. UNICEF Market</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.market.unicefusa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-14951\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shop-now4.jpg?resize=75%2C20\" alt=\"shop-now4\" width=\"75\" height=\"20\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.market.unicefusa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16756\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/UNICEF-Market.png?resize=600%2C369\" alt=\"UNICEF Market\" width=\"600\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/UNICEF-Market.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/UNICEF-Market.png?resize=300%2C184&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Ten Thousand Villages</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.tenthousandvillages.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-14951\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shop-now4.jpg?resize=75%2C20\" alt=\"shop-now4\" width=\"75\" height=\"20\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.tenthousandvillages.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16747\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Ten-Thousand-Villages.png?resize=600%2C337\" alt=\"Ten Thousand Villages\" width=\"600\" height=\"337\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Ten-Thousand-Villages.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Ten-Thousand-Villages.png?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></h2>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. St. Jude&#8217;s Giftshop</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://giftshop.stjude.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16821\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/shop.jpg?resize=75%2C20\" alt=\"shop\" width=\"75\" height=\"20\" /></a></